area_name: Dairy Farm / Frog Pond Boulders, The

content.description: Using the cow chips slab, start between Lactose and Frog Pond. Climb the slopping arete and top out without using Frog Pond for assistance.
content.location: Behind Dairy Farms go down the Calf Practice Wall flake routes.

content.description: Start crossed hands on the good edges, high foot layback into the first moves. Pull up and over to the crack edge and you're home free
content.protection: Bring a couple of crash pads and a spotter and you should be good
content.location: Lactose boulder in the middle of the face that faces the Frog Pond Boulder. Just to the right of the rib.

content.description: Grab the left leaning flake, go up for a knob, top it out.
content.location: On the south east face of the largest boulder in the Dairy Farm. Directly to the left of the waist high boulders in the flat clearing.

content.description: Begin low on the right leaning blunt arete. Using the arete and crystals on the face, make your way up and top out on the gigantic jug rail.
content.location: To the right of Milk Jugs, at the back of the corridor on the eastern end of the Dairy Farm.

content.description: Located on Lactose Boulder to the right of Milk Belly and Borden Arete.  There's a shallow corner right of the arete.
Start just right of the Southeastern blunt arete on the Frog Pond Boulder.  Start with a right hand on the rounded sloper, do the funky mantle and move straight up to finish it.
content.location: Southeast blunt arete on the Frog Pond Boulder

content.description: The obvious Prow on the East face of Haagen Das Boulder.  This is the jump start to the lip and mantle up.
content.location: Southeast face of Haagen Das boulder.

content.description: From The Little Dome Driver: In the crouch version, somehow get onto the Prow with your feet down low on the boulder and hands on both sides of the blunt arete, in a crouching position. Make your way as quickly as possible and with as few moves as possible to the lip and mantle up on top.
content.location: Southeast corner (prow) of Haagen Das boulder in the Dairy Farm.

content.description: Right of Layback 101 is a large knob.  Start on the knob and move up from there.  Hardest part is the start.
jump start mantle, right of Udderly Fantastic
content.location: Down climb Milk Money Offwidth

content.description: Around corner from Milk Moustache. Climb the Offwidth with a standing start, then topping out. Sit start for a harder variety.
content.location: Down climb this route is the way off all problems here.

content.description: Around corner from Milk Moustache, right of offwidth
content.location: Easiest descent is the Milk Money offwidth

content.description: Sit start with hands matched on the obvious mouth jug. A tricky heel hook / mantle balancing act will pull you through the crux. The rock is pretty good, but you may pull off a crystal or two while heel hooking.
content.location:
Located on the Frog Pond Boulder. When facing the Dairy Farm from the approach trail, it is the first large boulder on the right. The problem is located on the backside, the first problem on the left as you enter the corridor. 

  Look for the obvious mouth jug!

content.description: A good chimney that is located between Lactose Boulder and Blue Bell Boulder.
A left leaning crack behind a small tree.  Start low and work your up and to the left.
content.protection: A crash pad (or two).  The landing isn't great with some rocks, tree, and roots.
content.location: On the north east face of Dairy Farm Boulder

content.description: Easy Flake that has varied ratings in the books.
content.location: Right of High on the Food Chain

content.description: Right of Mild Cheddar
Start low on the big right arching flake and go right on underclings to the right side of the prow then top it out.
content.location: On the uphill side of the Dairy Farm boulders, it is a very obvious, strange looking flake.

content.description: Dihedral to the left of Blue Bell Arete
Sit down start on right side of the Western slabby face of the Frog Pond Boulder.  Move up and to the right to the blunt arete and then top it out.
content.location: Western, slabby face of the Frog Pond Boulder in the Dairy Farm.

content.description: Blunt arete to the right of Vitamin Fortified on the Lactose Boulder.  Tricky start getting up and onto the boulder. After you move up and onto the boulder it gets easier.
content.location: Southern, blunt arete of the Lactose boulder. To the left of Cottage Cheese face and to the right of Vitamin Fortified.

content.description: Right of the Prow

This route starts on two slopers/crimps to the right of Schmantle Fest.  It is also around the corner and to the left of Frogatron.  Jump to the two slopers, mantle and make your way to the top via more slopers and tiny edges.
content.location: Southern face of the Frog Pond Boulder

content.description: Start on the good crimp and head straight up to top out (as opposed to moving right to finish on Frogatron, V1).
content.location: On the frog pond boulder, likely the first problem you will see as you approach the boulder.

content.description: Start sitting under the crack and grab the undercling. Fight your way to the top!
content.location: Obvious, slightly overhanging hand crack to the right of the prow in the north east area (side that faces Turkey Peak) of the Dairy Farm boulders.

content.description: slab on Frog Pond Boulder
Climb the right side of the rounded arete using a series of heel hooks, side pulls, and the arete itself. Don't escape onto the slab to the left of the arete or it isn't a true ascent!
content.protection: Several trees and a jumble of boulders make the landing is bad on this one, but a few attentive spotters and crash pads make it ok. I wouldn't want to fall from up high on this one though.
content.location: On the eastern most side of the Dairy Farm boulders, look for a rounded arete behind trees with a jumble of boulders at the base.

content.description: Takes about 5 seconds to climb, warm up route.
Slab right of Milk Money
This is on the east face of Lactose Boulder.  Start on a small rock on the left side of a small tree.  Short face climb but with great crystals and knobs.
content.protection: Bouldering pad and maybe a spotter

content.description: Prettymuch anywhere on the uphill side of the main boulder.
On Frog Pond Boulder (on the corner where the frong pond boulder meets the dairy boulder, on the right of the slab climb on dairy boulder)
immediately right of Milk Belly
Climb the face using the blunt arete for the right hand and small crystals for the left.
content.protection: The route is short and has a nice soft landing so a pad might be optional.
content.location: This problem is right between the two dihedral problems Ice Cream Sandwich and Ice Cream Corner.  It starts on the face just left of the prominent blunt arete.

pathTokens: Dairy Farm / Frog Pond Boulders, The

content.description:
The Dairy Farm (AKA, Frog Pond) boulders offer the highest density of quality boulder problems within any area of E-Rock. From beginner to advanced, you can find a project here.  

  This area is almost always sunny, so its a good winter climbing spot. In the summer it can be a bit of a suffer fest.  

  Most of the problems are short, but quality. If you don't have a crash pad, this is a good place to go because most of the landings are flat and the top outs are low.
